Turkish 12-Month Inflation Forecast Falls to 6.73 Percent

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-09-22T11:33:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/turkish-12-month-inflation-forecast-falls-to-6-73-percent.html
Turkish forecasts for inflation
fell in a central bank fortnightly survey of economists and
business leaders.  Inflation in 12 months time was expected at 6.73 percent
compared with an estimate of 6.83 percent two weeks ago, the
central bank in Ankara said on its website today. Inflation in
24 months was foreseen at 6.26 percent compared with a previous
6.34 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
